---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

// Update this whenever the terms change.
const lastUpdated = 'June 19, 2026';
const contactEmail = 'huezo.dev@gmail.com';
---

<Layout
  title="Terms & Conditions — Shopping List by AI"
  description="Terms & Conditions for the Shopping List by AI Android app."
>
  <article class="legal container">
    <header class="legal-header">
      <h1>Terms &amp; Conditions</h1>
      <p class="legal-updated">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
    </header>

    <p>
      These Terms &amp; Conditions (&ldquo;Terms&rdquo;) govern your use of the
      <strong>Shopping List by AI</strong> mobile app (the &ldquo;App&rdquo;). By
      downloading, installing, or using the App, you agree to these Terms. If you
      do not agree, please do not use the App.
    </p>

    <h2>Use of the App</h2>
    <p>
      Shopping List by AI is a free tool that lets you create and manage shopping
      lists on your device. You may use the App for your personal, non-commercial
      purposes. You agree to use it only in ways that are lawful and that do not
      misuse or interfere with the App.
    </p>

    <h2>Your content</h2>
    <p>
      Any lists, products, and categories you create in the App belong to you and
      are stored locally on your device. We do not access, collect, or back up
      this content. You are solely responsible for your content and for keeping
      your own backups if you wish to retain it.
    </p>

    <h2>No account required</h2>
    <p>
      The App does not require you to create an account or provide personal
      information. Because your data lives only on your device, we cannot recover
      it if it is lost, for example after uninstalling the App or clearing its
      data.
    </p>

    <h2>Intellectual property</h2>
    <p>
      The App, including its name, design, and software, is owned by the developer
      and is protected by applicable laws. These Terms do not grant you any right
      to use our trademarks, logo, or branding without prior written permission.
    </p>

    <h2>Availability and changes</h2>
    <p>
      We may update, modify, or discontinue the App or any of its features at any
      time, with or without notice. We are not liable to you or any third party
      for any such change or discontinuation.
    </p>

    <h2>Disclaimer of warranties</h2>
    <p>
      The App is provided on an &ldquo;as is&rdquo; and &ldquo;as available&rdquo;
      basis, without warranties of any kind, whether express or implied. We do not
      warrant that the App will be uninterrupted, error-free, or free of harmful
      components, or that it will meet your specific requirements.
    </p>

    <h2>Limitation of liability</h2>
    <p>
      To the maximum extent permitted by law, the developer shall not be liable
      for any indirect, incidental, special, or consequential damages, or for any
      loss of data, arising out of or related to your use of the App.
    </p>

    <h2>Third-party stores</h2>
    <p>
      If you download the App from the Google Play Store, your use is also subject
      to the applicable store&rsquo;s terms and policies, in addition to these
      Terms.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes to these Terms</h2>
    <p>
      We may revise these Terms from time to time. When we do, we will update the
      &ldquo;Last updated&rdquo; date at the top of this page. Continued use of the
      App after changes are posted means you accept the updated Terms.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact us</h2>
    <p>
      If you have any questions about these Terms, you can reach us at
      <a href={`mailto:${contactEmail}`}>{contactEmail}</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .legal {
    max-width: 760px;
    padding-block: var(--space-5xl);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-size: 17px;
  }

  .legal-header {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3xl);
  }

  .legal h1 {
    font-size: clamp(32px, 5vw, 44px);
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .legal-updated {
    margin-top: var(--space-sm);
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 15px;
  }

  .legal h2 {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-size: 22px;
    margin-top: var(--space-3xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .legal p {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .legal strong {
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .legal a {
    color: var(--primary-light);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }

  .legal a:hover {
    color: var(--accent);
  }
</style>
